    'Melt butter in a pot over medium heat; add chopped onion and minced garlic and sauté 5-6 minutes until the onion is soft and translucent and the garlic is fragrant.',
    'Add 6 chopped tomatoes and 2 cups vegetable stock; bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce to medium-low and simmer 15-18 minutes until the tomatoes completely break down and the flavors meld.',
    'Remove from heat and blend the soup until completely smooth using an immersion blender or countertop blender; return to the pot.',
    'Simmer the blended soup on low heat for 5 minutes until it reaches a velvety consistency that coats a spoon.',
    'Stir in 1/4 cup cream off the heat and season with salt; the soup should be rich, coral-colored, and silky smooth.',
    'Serve hot in bowls; the texture should be creamy with no tomato chunks remaining.',
